{
  "buggy_files": ["drivers/acpi/video_detect.c"],
  "buggy_functions": ["video_detect_dmi_table"],
  "confidence": 0.95,
  "reasoning": "The Acer TravelMate 5735Z is missing from the DMI quirks table in video_detect.c. By default, the backlight detection logic (acpi_video_get_backlight_type()) returns acpi_backlight_video for this system because: (1) the system has ACPI_VIDEO_BACKLIGHT capability, (2) it is not a Windows 8 ready BIOS, and (3) no DMI quirk exists to override this. This causes the system to use the ACPI video backlight driver instead of the native backlight (intel_backlight). However, the ACPI video backlight doesn't properly control brightness on this hardware. When users boot with acpi_backlight=native, the native backlight works correctly with 15-16 levels instead of the default ACPI video interface. The fix requires adding the Acer TravelMate 5735Z (sys_vendor='Acer', product_name='TravelMate 5735Z', board_name='BA51_MV') to the video_detect_dmi_table with a callback to video_detect_force_native() to force it to use the native backlight interface that actually works on this hardware."
}

